< Text>
I took my mother to Sprouts on 4/30/2021 around 3pm. She is elderly, so I bagged her groceries and paid with her credit card.  I paid separately for my bulgar wheat.  I told the cashier, "sorry" because I handed him a 20 dollar bill. (Why charge one item?)  Anyway, he gave me change back as if I paid with a $10 bill.  I looked at him and said, "I gave you a twenty!"  I know I gave him a twenty because I did not have any tens, having just gone out to lunch and paid tip with $1 bills.
He looked at me and with a flat expression said, "What would you like me to do?"  I could tell then, that it was going to be a losing battle, my word against his.  He was rather heavy set.  I am telling every one I know to not patronize that place.  My mom lives in Los Altos and we will shop at Safeway from now on.  I am so upset.<//Text>

<Name>Haylee Jane Monteiro<//Name><gmap_id>0x808fb09c3f96d667:0xb7720e960b510149<//gmap_id><Response>None< /Response><date>1573578559103</date><user>105327052402786414889</user>< rating>
5< /rating>
< text>
These guys are are just the best. I only just discovered Sprouts after living in this area for over a year now, and I already regret all the time I missed out on.
Their product line is just amazing, and they've got everything you could need. It might seem bare bones are first since the store is on the smaller side and just has a few brands, but when you look closer, they're the right brands for the product and prices are pretty pretty good.
My favorite part is honestly their bulk section. I used to go to the Whole Foods around the corner, but no more. These guys are always stocked up, and with quality items. A recent experience I had was with buying Nutritional Yeast. I really use a lot of it and used to get it from Whole Foods bulk since it was the cheapest but still tasted so much better than the bottled ones our there. But they had been out for weeks. I called every day asking about availability and after the 2nd week the person told me the distributor was out and didn't know when they would get any back. I was really upset and started researching other places to buy it on Amazon, but somehow (and thankfully) I remembered that Sprouts has a bulk section too. I called the store and they confirmed they had some. I went in and it was just the right kind I wanted. That amazing taste at also a low price. I'm not kidding, I bought over a pound of it.
The staff is also quite nice here. I've called on multiple occasions asking about product availability and prices (since I would need to travel 15 minutes there and back and wouldn't want to go home disappointed), evd and they were always quick to answer the call (unlike some other stores that would put you on hold forever) and would actually go to the aisles and come back with all the info I needed.
Going to be the first stop on all my grocery runs now.< /text>

<Time>1578853793716</Time><rate>4</rate>< UserId.>
105931411578761345245< /UserId.>
<Response>None</Response><user_name>Thomas Bakker<//user_name>< Review>
With everything that we're experiencing here in Northern California telling us that climate change is real, and that we need to reduce our dependence on centralized power generation, we decided to do our part and go solar.  We had been contemplating adding solar for a while so when Joe from High Definition Solar knocked on our door a week after we had been off power for 3 days thanks to a PG&E power shut off, we were ready to buy.  We went with High Definition because we felt they had the best technology, were reassured by the 4 diamond rating and the people we met with were knowledgeable and informative.  Like any project, there were a few minor hitches but it's clear that everybody involved cares about the customer, believes in the value of solar and wants to do the right thing.  Despite the hitches, the panels were installed promptly and have been working perfectly since day 1.  The one thing that could have been given more attention to is the location of the controller box and the routing of conduit.   We would have preferred a less intrusive and less visible location for the box, the box intrudes into a narrow passage, and for the conduit routed to more closely follow the contours of the house.  I hope that in the future the project managers and installers will spend more time with the customer to help them understand this aspect of the installation.  Nevertheless, I would recommend High Definition Solar to anybody who is considering rooftop solar.</Review>

This company called my 80+ year old parents to let them know that they needed 6 more panels.  My parents had no idea if they needed them or not.  (NOT)  To my brother and I that is unthinkable.  It is an investment over time, but come on.  REALLY!  They are in their 80's and are in failing health, with Visiting Angel and VA nursing helping them seven days a week.

When final payment came due, we were brought up to date on the situation and found out that High Definition Solar kept calling my parents until they agreed to meet with them.  The VA nurse said that they pressured my parents until they agreed to purchase over $13,000 worth of additional panels.They certainly did not need to spend anymore money for something that would not have a long term benefit from.

Now they have 12 panels on the house and no longer live there because they moved to assisted living.  And this all occurred in less than six months after they were persuaded to add more panels.

This is absolutely outrageous and this company should be ashamed of themselves and of their employees.

We did contact an attorney and we were told that small claims court was our only option.  I am still considering pursuing legal action.<//Review>

< rating>
1</rating>
<Text>Stay away from this company! I had a friend that was employed by them who informed be about their business practices and they are appalling. First of all, they deliberately lie to their employees that go door to door to setup appointments who have minimal training and little understanding of Solar Power options. Based on the lies they are told by the company they will repeat them and mislead those they are speaking with.  They have a huge amount of employee turnover since those who do any research of their own get tired of peddling lies, those who stay often do so because they have little other employment options.

They tell their employees that they are able to install systems fit to anyone's needs and that anyone as low as a $100 monthly electric bill can save money. The fact of the matter is that they have a minimum requirement on the panels that they will install which is far in excess of what someone with such low energy usage would require. They also state that they use the most advanced solar technology available which is really just the industry standard. They try to state that the microinverters they use are far superior to a standard inverter system but conceal the additional long term costs involved with this system or the fact that microinverters are not necessarily the ideal solution for all systems. They also lie and state that homes with significant tree coverage throughout the day will generate much more energy than they actually they would because of their "magic" microinverters. They also train their employees to hound anyone they speak with for an appointment regardless of how inconvenient the time may be for the homeowner.

Additionally, they will claim that they are running a special promotional program that they always "just started" and is available for a "limited time" when it is always running. They will only schedule a sales meeting if all homeowners are present because they want to close the deal on the first meeting. They will pretend to offer a special discount that is only available if you make the purchase that day. Thus, it is a high pressure sales tactic. Additionally, if you cancel the meeting or decide to pass, expect to receive follow up calls for months.

They try to state that they are specially qualified because they are Diamond Certified but this is little different than paying for any other "seal of approval" like the Better Business Bureau accreditation, just from a more obscure organization with a flashier name.

If you want to have Solar panels installed there are many other contractors who will do so for much cheaper (albeit with a lesser warranty) or other much larger and established companies that will be around the same price level. Do not reward a company with such shady business practices.< /Text><pictures>None</pictures><Response>None<//Response><gmap_id>0x808566c2232c28fd:0x5a4349f2e9549b74< /gmap_id></record>
</dataset><record>

< text>
I am so pleased with High Definition Solar and how they helped us save over $300+/month on our energy bill. From the initial contact, to the salespeople, to the installers and the customer followup they were personable, honest and capable in their professionalism.
The fact that they were first, and continue to be, a roofing company that also installs solar was a big selling point. I feel that the integrity of my roof has not been compromised by the fasteners that secure the panels to the roof because it has all been flashed and sealed properly. I love the fact that the solar units are in parrallel instead of in series and that each panel has it's own inverter; it's just better engineering. I also think that owning the panels outright, getting the government rebate, and having no easement on my roof is an honest and straightforward marketing and business model. This company did just what they said they would do, at the quoted price, in the time they said they woud do it and left not one scrap of mess behind. I will recommend this High Definition Solar to anyone who asks me about my decision to go solar.< /text>

<user_id>102126942788609579687<//user_id><Name>Lucas Koch< /Name><Time>1520470542857< /Time>< rating>
5</rating>
< review>
We have been going to Blue Rock for a few years now as we need materials for our home projects. I have yet to have a negative experience of any kind. I think the prices are fair, and quality of all the different materials we've picked up and had delivered leaves nothing to complain about.  The staff is always friendly and accommodating. We started using them for a few cubic yards of garden dirt to fill above ground planters in a garden house i built. No problems with the quality of dirt. Plants and veggies grew fine. For our most recent large project, we completely re-landscaped our front yard to low water, rock and drought tolerant plants. We wanted some variance and topography to imitate the southwest region. We did all the work ourselves but all the rock material came from Blue Rock. We had several yards of a few different types of rock delivered.  The driver did a good job dropping the rock off, keeping the different types separated which made things easier for us. The end result has promoted many compliments from neighbors and friends. While we did the work, I must say we're glad to have used Blue Rock for materials that look great and made the landscape reno affordable. We'll be using them again very soon for our backyard landscape, now that our pool is done. Thanks Blue Rock, and we'll see you again soon!</review>

<user>105323303646006083809<//user><user_name>Bob Smith<//user_name><Time>1445648080992</Time><Rating>1<//Rating>< text>
I would give a -10 stars if I could. These people seem nice until we had an issue with their product and then they turn into the worst nightmare we've ever had. We were supposed to get some small colored rock, basically like colored P gravel, they told my wife before they delivered it-that it had not been washed yet. What we ended up with was dirt mixed with the p-gravel type rock. We told them the rock was basically 25 to 35% dirt. We paid laborers to install the rock, then we tried to wash the rock, what we ended up with was rock embedded in mud. Basically we are doing a low water landscaping and the whole idea is to not have weeds growing as well. We put down the weed barrier and then of course the rock material goes on top of the weed barrier. The material they sent was so full of dirt basically weeds would have germinated in the dirt they sent us and the weed roots would have gone through the weed barrier. We asked them to come back and take the faulty material away and refund us the cost on that part of the materials we order only. I told them not only did I have to pay the labor to put the material down and I now have to pay the labor to take material out. To get a refund they basically told me I would have to load up about 12 yards of material, ship it back to them which is 25 miles away to get a refund. Then the owner agreed he would have the delivery truck come back which just left my house about 15 minutes earlier if I would pay my guys the labor to shovel material back into his truck. After tense conversation I agreed to eat about 240 in labor due to their faulty material just to get a refund of about 400 on the faulty material. After they had their truck driver come back, my guys spent 1 1/2 hours loading up this companies faulty  material,  my wife gets a call from this place telling us they were going to charge us a 20% restocking fee and here's the reason why.  They said they had a pay their driver for the extra hour that he had to wait while we paid our guys labor to load up their truck with their faulty material. I called them and I was not too nice and I let them know that I've already absorb costs on labor here because of their faulty materials and that we were not paying the 20% restocking fee and that that was never agreed to. The owners daughter who was belligerent, would not even let me talk, every time I tried to explain; all she did is over talk me and tell me I won't listen to her, I wouldn't listen because she kept saying the same thing she was saying before which was not acceptable.  These people expected us to adsorb costs and time and energy because of their faulty material, and then wanted us to pay for their truck drivers time or a 20% restocking fee and for us to absorb labor for their mistake. These people are bad business people, please beware; they are nice until they have your money, but if they make a mistake it's the person buying their materials fault not theirs. The root cause of the issue was, on the morning of our delivery they told my wife that one of the products they have, small P gravel type rock had not been washed yet and offered a $10 discount per yard. They didn't tell my wife that basically it was 25 to 35% dirt, they said not washed. Instead they said it's not our fault, it's your wife's fault because we told her it had not been washed and she accepted, thinking that we can relate not washed to 25 to 35% dirt. My wife expectations was we are getting the small P gravel type rock that would have basically a coating of dust or a light coating of dirt. But what we ended up with was basically P gravel type rock mixed with about 25-35% dirt and when we tried to wash the dirt off of the small rock we basically ended up with small p gravel type rock embedded in mud. Would you want that at your home?< /text>

Elizabeth Blount</Name>
<time>1552249025779< /time>< Rating>
4< /Rating>
< review>
Hidden gem. Just my kind of "frou-frou" breakfast, my husband would call it. First of all its at the end of this non-descript strip mall next to O'Reilly's and a few vacant business suites. Inside, though, the place has a nice rustic look to it with wood beams hanging from the ceiling and the ambience made cozy by a faux fireplace by the seating area with leather love seat and a trio of hammered copper coffee tables. The orange juice is freshly squeezed. I had the Chylls waffle with just enough fresh fruit and whipped cream on top. The bacon was crisped just the way I like it.
But why 4-stars you asked? Maybe because my husband had sourdough toast and they didn't have jam. Oh well. Doesn't keep me from coming back.
I'm excited to try their boba teas of which they have quite a selection. Next time we drive by....
Great job, Chyll people. Great job.<//review>

Brandon Tyrrell</name>
< Date>
1554146254926</Date>
<rate>4< /rate>< text>
4 Stars because the finished product is always picture perfect and consistently tastes the same.

My 3 Gripes.

1. I came here for breakfast once and at 8 in the morning, there was modern hip-hop/rap music playing talking about all sorts of derogatory and expletive things. Not something you should hear at a family business.

2. Get these workers some padded mats to stand on, standing stationary on hard tile will only fatigue employees.

3. EVERY time I come here just to grab some ice cream or a quick drink, even when there's only a total of 3 people in the building, I always get the "sorry for the wait" after being handed by drink/meal. Not sure if that's because of the work involved when crafting takes up so much time. But the last time I was here I waited just over 20 minutes for a smoothie.

It's a great place to grab a treat and take your family to visit when they travel from out of town. It's clean with a nice atmosphere. I enjoy coming here just to grab something and head out. But it's got a few areas that could use some improvement.< /text>

Their soups are amazing! The Tiger Tea with boba is my favorite drink (many to choose from). To satisfy your sweet tooth, may I suggest one of their 'rolled ice cream' desserts. I'm off to go get my tea!</review>

< Text>
The service was great, I felt very taken care of. The wait for my rolls wasn't too long, and the quality was good. The price was a little high, but the portions and roll sizes mostly make up for that. I gave it 4 out of 5 stars because I've gone to other places that are just to die for and that I can't live without, where here is a good place, but if asked where my FAVORITE place for sushi is, this placed missed that mark. That being said, if I'm craving sushi and am in the area, I would eat here again. Nothing negative to say, just not my #1 favorite place to go.< /Text>

1342555479471</time>
< Rate>

<Review>I live in Las Vegas and we have a good handful of Sushi restaurants here worth eating at - I have 1 favorite and about 5 that I would go to regularly. That being said, I am visiting family here in Rancho Cucamonga and decided to take the wife somewhere based off local reviews. I can say that if this is the best there is locally - its a wonder how this place is even open. Upon arrival we were not even greeted once by the 2 sushi chefs when we sat down - the 2 girls working in the front that were taking the orders for the sushi chefs for some reason had no clue how to answer any questions I was asking them about sashimi or sushi. I eventually told them I would just order from the chefs directly - except for one thing, that never happened since after about 10-15 more minutes the chefs never asked what we wanted.
Finally after just ordering from the hostess girls in front (sashimi plate, special rolls, spicy ponzu and 2 beers) they finally brought our order. The fish was pretty fresh which I do expect in SoCal, but the sauce for the rolls and the so called excuse for spicy ponzu was a weak effort to say the least. Maybe soy sauce with sriracha added? We finished our beers pretty quickly and waited and watched the hostess girls walk by us 10 times each never to ask if we wanted more drinks and never picked up our empty plates to ask if we wanted to order more. Needless to say there was maybe 10-15 people in the place at 6pm so there was no excuse. Tips and bills are ran up from good service...example being more alcohol to customers at a fast pace and clearing plates for more rolls to come in. Neither done in this case.

This cant be the best sushi in Rancho by any means - this place wouldnt last 3-6 months in Las Vegas without going out of business. I explained my concern to the hostess when we left since we were dis-satisfied, but she didnt seem to care much. Good luck with your business - will probably be a short run.<//Review>< pics>
None</pics>

Haven't been here for awhile and no drive in dining when I was there during orange tier. Only drive thru available but not a huge problem.
Huge selection of food, drinks, and dessert. Prices are not bad overall but can add up because of the temptation for a shake or slushie.

I would come here more often if it wasn't so far from my home. There should be more Sonic around.
I highly recommend this place for a quick bite and/or for the drinks.<//text>

<review>Last week I stopped here to get iced coffee. I came through the drive-thru and ordered several drinks during their morning drink promotion, which is heavily advertised. Despite these advertisements I was charged full price. I let the employee know that the signs say the drinks are discounted until 10am, so she reluctantly changed the prices. I drove away and when I tasted my coffee it was 100% cream. No coffee. I was already on the freeway so I chalked it up as a loss.
2 weeks later I made the mistake of returning around the same time, but this time I ordered  different beverages. I was still charged full price during the promotional hours. The same employee was working the window, but this time there was someone else with her. So I again pointed out the discrepancy. The other employee changed the price for me while the reluctant one went out to read the sign, because she seemed to once again think I was wrong.
No discount is really worth the headache. I probably won't stop here again even though it's convenient with my commute.<//review>< Response>

Usually I like Sonic, but for some reason tonight was exceptionally awful

I ordered a pretzel dog with cheese and bacon, which was okay

But the sole reason I actually went there, was because I wanted a blue raspberry nerds slushie, I got the slushie, but there are no nerds in it! i'm finishing it right now hoping maybe they're all caught somewhere in the middle and it wasn't blended or something, but i'm losing faith as i get closer to the bottom of the cup and still see and taste NO NERDS!

My girlfriend wanted tater tots and a grilled cheese, I told her the tater tots are bomb, because they usually are, and i told her additionally, you really can't mess up grilled cheese.

Well now my girlfriend thinks i'm an idiot, because the tater tots were unsalted and not hot, and the grilled cheese was straight up slightly melted american cheese between two squishy ass pieces of NOT HOT white bread, so basically a kind of melted cheese sandwich, definitely no grilled in there, no butter on the outside of the bread, like how do you even do that...

it's like ordering a cheese burger and getting a mcchicken, just bland and not quite right.

So now my girlfriend is making me sit through the drive thru at the mcdonalds across the street, which is terrible to ever go to since it's way too damn small for the amount of people that want to go there, thanks to the in n out across from it not having a drive thru and the other nearby restaurants being expensive and not that good

Yeah i'm talking to you El Pollo Loco...fml</Review>
